# Cursor Rules — Cafe Delight Admin Panel (Laravel + Filament)

## 0) Prime Directive
- Build the **Restaurant Admin Panel ONLY** first.
- Use **Filament** for all admin UI.
- Keep changes **small, reviewable, and testable**.
- Never introduce customer-portal pages/routes until admin panel MVP is complete.

---

## 1) Tech Constraints
- Backend: **Laravel (latest stable)**
- Admin UI: **Filament**
- DB: **MySQL** (use migrations, never edit DB manually)
- Images: **Spatie Media Library** (store to `public` disk for MVP)
- Auth: Filament auth + **spatie/laravel-permission** for roles
- Use Laravel **Form Requests** for non-Filament endpoints (if any).
- Prefer **Enums** for statuses (OrderStatus, OfferType, OfferScope).

---

## 2) Coding Standards (MANDATORY)
- Strict typing wherever possible (PHP 8+ features).
- Follow PSR-12 + run **Laravel Pint** before commits.
- No `dd()`, no debug prints, no commented-out code.
- Keep controllers thin; push logic to:
  - `Actions/` (single-purpose classes)
  - `Services/` (reusable business logic)
  - `Observers/` (only when needed)
- Prefer query scopes in models for repeated filters.

---

## 3) Database & Models Rules
- Every feature change that needs data must include:
  - migration + model + relationships + factories (optional later)
- Use these core tables (do not rename without reason):
  - `categories`
  - `menu_items`
  - `offers`
  - `orders`
  - `order_items`
- Orders must store **snapshot fields** in `order_items`:
  - `name_snapshot`, `price_snapshot`
  (Prices/name changes must not affect old orders.)
- Always include `created_at/updated_at` and sensible indexes:
  - `menu_items(category_id, is_available)`
  - `offers(is_active, start_at, end_at)`
  - `orders(status, created_at)`

---

## 4) Filament Rules (Admin UX)
- Use Filament Resources for CRUD:
  - CategoryResource
  - MenuItemResource
  - OfferResource
  - OrderResource
- Must include:
  - clean navigation labels + icons
  - searchable tables
  - filters (status/active/category)
  - bulk actions where safe (e.g., toggle availability)
- Forms must:
  - validate required fields
  - use helpful placeholders + helper text
  - keep layout clean (sections, columns)
- Orders page must support:
  - status update action
  - print-friendly view link/action

---

## 5) Security & Authorization
- Admin area must be protected:
  - Only users with role `owner` or `staff` can access Filament.
- Use **Policies** for models if needed.
- Never expose admin APIs publicly.
- Validation is required on all writes.

---

## 6) Business Logic Rules
- Menu Items:
  - `is_available` controls visibility to customers later
  - `is_featured` used for home highlights later
- Offers:
  - must support schedule (start/end)
  - must support scope (all / category / items)
- Orders:
  - statuses are a strict workflow:
    `received -> preparing -> ready -> out_for_delivery -> delivered`
    plus `cancelled`
  - status changes must be auditable (store `status_updated_at` at least)

---

## 7) File/Folder Organization
- Models: `app/Models`
- Filament resources: `app/Filament/Resources`
- Enums: `app/Enums`
- Actions: `app/Actions`
- Services: `app/Services`
- Policies: `app/Policies`
- Database migrations: `database/migrations`

Do not create random folders.

---

## 8) Git Workflow Rules
- One step = one commit.
- Commit messages must be imperative:
  - `feat(admin): add Category resource`
  - `feat(admin): add MenuItem resource with images`
  - `feat(admin): add Order status workflow`
  - `fix(admin): validate offer date range`
- Never mix refactors with feature work unless required.

---

## 9) Output Rules (How Cursor should respond)
When implementing a step, Cursor must provide:
- What files changed (list)
- What was added/removed (short)
- How to verify manually in the browser (Filament path + clicks)
- Migration commands to run (if applicable)

No long explanations, no tutorials, no unrelated improvements.

---

## 10) Definition of Done (Admin Panel MVP)
Admin panel is considered "done" only when:
- Admin can login
- Admin can manage Categories, Menu Items (with images), Offers
- Admin can view Orders + update status + print view
- Role-based access is enforced
- No obvious UI/validation gaps in admin flows
